### Enrichment
Classic homemade lemon curd needs only 5 ingredients: lemons, eggs, sugar, salt, and butter. Cook slowly over medium heat whisking constantly to prevent scrambling eggs. Takes about 15 minutes. Ready when it thickens and coats back of wooden spoon. Use fresh organic lemons (not bottled juice) since you need the zest. Cold butter helps cool and set curd quickly. Store in airtight jar in fridge 7-10 days or freeze up to 3 months. Much better than store-bought.

